Queue Screen¶

Contains the functions needed on the screen queue.

class queued.CheckableQueue(maxsize=0)[source]¶

Bases: queue.Queue

Queue with additional __contains__() method, so one can check if item is already in queue.

class queued.QueuedRoot(**kwargs)[source]¶

Bases: kivy.uix.floatlayout.FloatLayout

Root widget for the queue-screen.

add_waiting(self, word)[source]¶

Add word in "waiting" state, waiting to be queued.

choose_file_to_import(self, button)[source]¶

Open an instance of MDFileManager to let user choose a file to import.

Binds function to clicking on file, so the import is started in separate thread.

click_on_item(self, item)[source]¶

Dependent of the current_state of the item performs appropriate action.

dequeue_word(self, word)[source]¶

Change state to "waiting" and adds word to stale so it will be skipped in queue.

dialog[source]¶

ObjectProperty. Instance of custom_widgets.dialogs.CustomDialog.

dialog_callback(self, btn_txt, words)[source]¶

Add words to queue if "OK"-button was pressed.

import_from(self, path, source='kindle')[source]¶

Import, process and queue words from file.

If non-dictionary forms are detected, prompts the user with suggestions for replacement.

Parameters

  • path – Path to file.

  • source – Type of source. Options=[“kindle”,”txt”] (Default value = “kindle”)

DictProperty of the form {"icon_name":"Help text"}.

Check if word is in queue.

Empty the queue. Worker stop after finishing current task.

stale[source]¶

Set of stale words, i.e. words that have been dequeued and will be skipped if appearing in the queue.

start_downloading(self, *_)[source]¶

If no worker is present, start a new one to download data.

static switch_to_single_word_screen(word)[source]¶

Switch to single_word to generate a card for the clicked word.

worker_single_word(self)[source]¶

Take a word from app.queue and process it, changing app.loading_state_dict accordingly.

Repeat as long as app.queue is not empty.
